review_blob: Dark colored beer reminiscent of the color of rich hard woods like those used in smoking rooms. Moderate head with large bubbles when poured from the bottle. While advertised, the rasin note is understated at best. Heavy malt flavor eventhough the top note is one of chocolate and caramel. Very crisp finish with a dry lingering finish that leaves you needing another sip.

Pours a rich, dark brown with a thick and frothy head. Primarily small bubbles. Top note of roasted malt with a hint of vanilla. Initial taste of roasted malt; reminiscent of bread and a dry earthy note. Carbonation seems to detract from the taste yet the mouth feel is smooth with a light, lingering hint of vanilla.
